            "content": {
                "raw": "I am in favor or (perhaps in 3.0) removing everything from yt/analysis_modules/api.py and mandating that analysis modules be imported from their specific api.py.  With the current setup, there is no way to know that the user was trying to specifically import the photon simulator or anything else since it seems that importing anything from analysis_modules/api.py executes all of the imports in there.",
                "html": "<p>I am in favor or (perhaps in 3.0) removing everything from yt/analysis_modules/api.py and mandating that analysis modules be imported from their specific api.py.  With the current setup, there is no way to know that the user was trying to specifically import the photon simulator or anything else since it seems that importing anything from analysis_modules/api.py executes all of the imports in there.</p>",
                "markup": "markdown"
            },
